<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,619,1111]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">
marine water strider 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1903" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[431,792,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Halobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis box="[431,636,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Halobates sexualis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[646,792,619,643]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="223 - 272" refId="ref918" refString="Distant, W. L. (1903) Report on the Rhynchota. Part I. Heteroptera. Fasciculi Malayenses, Zoology, 1 (Part II), 223 - 272." type="journal article" year="1903">Distant, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the estuary of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A15F5D59163C3936FF7CFDDE5B5EFE3B:2C29BA94163C3937FAF9FDDE5B81FD32" box="[1298,1436,619,643]" country="Malaysia" name="Jambu River" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Jambu River</location>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[158,301,655,679]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="223 - 272" refId="ref918" refString="Distant, W. L. (1903) Report on the Rhynchota. Part I. Heteroptera. Fasciculi Malayenses, Zoology, 1 (Part II), 223 - 272." type="journal article" year="1903">Distant 1903</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[718,816,655,679]" name="Malaysia" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, L." box="[830,964,655,679]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="111 - 135" refId="ref874" refString="Cheng, L. (1985) Biology of Halobates (Heteroptera: Gerridae). Annual Review of Entomology, 30 (1), 111 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1146 / annurev. en. 30.010185.000551" type="journal article" year="1985">Cheng 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel, H. &amp; Tran, A. D." box="[976,1185,655,679]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="279 - 295" refId="ref1278" refString="Zettel, H. &amp; Tran, A. D. (2009) First inventory of the water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of Langkawi Island, Kedah, Malaysia. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 57 (2), 279 - 295." type="journal article" year="2009">Zettel &amp; Tran 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ikawa, T. &amp; Okabe, H. &amp; Cheng, L." box="[1196,1386,655,679]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="915 - 936" refId="ref977" refString="Ikawa, T., Okabe, H. &amp; Cheng, L. (2012) Skaters of the seas-comparative ecology of nearshore and pelagic Halobates species (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with special reference to Japanese species. Marine Biology Research, 8 (10), 915 - 936. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000.2012.705848" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ikawa 
<emphasis box="[1268,1322,655,679]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry name="Sri Lanka" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A." box="[232,501,691,715]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="533 - 553" refId="ref800" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A. (1992) Sea skaters of India, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives, with a new species and a revised key to Indian Ocean species of Halobates and Asclepios (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Journal of Natural History, 26 (3), 533 - 553. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939200770341" type="journal article" year="1992">Andersen &amp; Foster 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ikawa, T. &amp; Okabe, H. &amp; Cheng, L." box="[512,701,691,715]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="915 - 936" refId="ref977" refString="Ikawa, T., Okabe, H. &amp; Cheng, L. (2012) Skaters of the seas-comparative ecology of nearshore and pelagic Halobates species (Hemiptera: Gerridae), with special reference to Japanese species. Marine Biology Research, 8 (10), 915 - 936. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000.2012.705848" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ikawa 
<emphasis box="[585,639,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[761,856,691,715]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roman-Palacios, C. &amp; Damgaard, J. &amp; Cheng, L. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. &amp; Ikawa, T. &amp; Weir, T. A. &amp; Zettel, H." box="[870,1173,691,715]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref1180" refString="Roman-Palacios, C., Damgaard, J., Cheng, L., Moreira, F. F. F., Ikawa, T., Weir, T. A. &amp; Zettel, H. (2018) Molecular phylogeny of sea-skaters (Halobates), relationship between Halobatini and Metrocorini, and a catalogue of the subfamily Halobatinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae). Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 1 (aop), 1 - 102. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 00002197" type="journal article" year="2018">
Román-Palacios 
<emphasis box="[1054,1108,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[1191,1213,692,715]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">In</collectorName>
the pioneering work by 
<bibRefCitation author="Herring, L." box="[186,347,727,751]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="225 - 305" refId="ref952" refString="Herring, L. (1961) The genus Halobates (Hemiptera: Gerridae). Pacific Insects, 3, 225 - 305." type="journal article" year="1961">Herring (1961)</bibRefCitation>
on this genus, he mentioned the 
<typeStatus box="[706,752,728,752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">type</typeStatus>
locality to be “Estuary of the Jambu River, Malaya.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A." pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="533 - 553" refId="ref800" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A. (1992) Sea skaters of India, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives, with a new species and a revised key to Indian Ocean species of Halobates and Asclepios (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Journal of Natural History, 26 (3), 533 - 553. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939200770341" type="journal article" year="1992">Andersen and Foster (1992)</bibRefCitation>
provided notes on the whereabouts of the 
<typeStatus box="[797,843,764,788]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species and mentioned that it was probably located in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A15F5D59163C3936FF7CFDDE5B5EFE3B:2C29BA94163C3937FED6FCAA5FF2FC86" box="[317,495,799,823]" country="Thailand" municipality="Kuala Jambu" name="northern Malaya" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">northern Malaya</location>
(
<collectingMunicipality box="[510,653,799,823]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Kuala Jambu</collectingMunicipality>
) immediately south of the border of 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1145,799,823]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
on the 
<collectorName box="[1227,1276,799,823]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Gulf</collectorName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1367,799,823]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Siam</collectingCountry>
coast. 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Cheng, L." box="[151,456,835,859]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="119 - 180" refId="ref739" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Cheng, L. (2004) The marine insect Halobates (Heteroptera: Gerridae): biology, adaptations, distribution, and phylogeny. Oceanography and Marine Biology: an Annual Review, 42, 119 - 180. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / 9780203507810. ch 5" type="journal article" year="2004">Andersen and Cheng (2004)</bibRefCitation>
further backed this up by mentioning 
<collectingCountry box="[873,971,835,859]" name="Malaysia" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
in the range of 
<emphasis box="[1145,1272,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[1145,1268,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Halobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">H. sexualis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which was not recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[315,413,871,895]" name="Malaysia" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
until 2009 (
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel, H. &amp; Tran, A. D." box="[549,765,871,895]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="279 - 295" refId="ref1278" refString="Zettel, H. &amp; Tran, A. D. (2009) First inventory of the water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of Langkawi Island, Kedah, Malaysia. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 57 (2), 279 - 295." type="journal article" year="2009">Zettel &amp; Tran 2009</bibRefCitation>
) but also stated that it was not verified personally. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[151,307,907,931]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="223 - 272" refId="ref918" refString="Distant, W. L. (1903) Report on the Rhynchota. Part I. Heteroptera. Fasciculi Malayenses, Zoology, 1 (Part II), 223 - 272." type="journal article" year="1903">Distant (1903)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the collection locality as “Estuary of the Jambu River, Jhering.” According to the Map of the Malay Peninsula published around the same time period in 1898 by Stanford, London (
<bibRefCitation author="RASGBI" box="[1083,1247,943,967]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1091" refString="RASGBI (1898) Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland. Straits Branch. &amp; Van Cuylenburg, John. &amp; Edward Stanford Ltd. 1898. A map of the Malay Peninsula [cartographic material]. Compiled by and published for the Straits Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society, Singapore; prepared and drawn by John van Cuylenburg, Singapore. Available from: http: // nla. gov. au / nla. obj- 231529372 (accessed 9 FJanuary F 2020)" type="url" year="1898">RASGBI 1898</bibRefCitation>
), Jambu or Jering is located along the coast of Yaring (formerly Jhering/Jering) which is a 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A15F5D59163C3936FF7CFDDE5B5EFE3B:2C29BA94163C3937FC43FC665A21FC5A" box="[936,1084,979,1003]" country="Thailand" name="District Town" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" stateProvince="Pattani">District Town</location>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1121,1298,979,1003]" country="Thailand" name="Pattani" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Pattani Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1335,1433,979,1003]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectorName box="[151,198,1015,1039]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">This</collectorName>
location is about 
<quantity box="[393,475,1015,1039]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" unit="km" value="120.0">120 km</quantity>
northwest of the previously presumed location by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A." box="[1024,1302,1015,1039]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" pagination="533 - 553" refId="ref800" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Foster, W. A. (1992) Sea skaters of India, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives, with a new species and a revised key to Indian Ocean species of Halobates and Asclepios (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Journal of Natural History, 26 (3), 533 - 553. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939200770341" type="journal article" year="1992">Andersen &amp; Foster (1992</bibRefCitation>
; see fig. 24) and is most likely the site of collection, which is in present-day 
<collectingCountry box="[830,928,1051,1075]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectorName box="[938,979,1051,1075]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">The</collectorName>
<typeStatus box="[986,1032,1052,1076]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species should thus be attributed to 
<collectingCountry box="[287,382,1087,1111]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
instead of 
<collectingCountry box="[500,601,1087,1111]" name="Malaysia" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974739" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3974739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3974739/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" startId="0.[151,244,1803,1825]" targetBox="[151,1436,1132,1774]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1803,1862]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,263,1803,1825]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. The original type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[556,738,1803,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Halobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis box="[556,738,1803,1824]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Halobates sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indicated with a yellow star and the assumed type locality with a red circle. Inset shows the map published in 1898 (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="RASGBI" box="[737,883,1840,1862]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1091" refString="RASGBI (1898) Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland. Straits Branch. &amp; Van Cuylenburg, John. &amp; Edward Stanford Ltd. 1898. A map of the Malay Peninsula [cartographic material]. Compiled by and published for the Straits Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society, Singapore; prepared and drawn by John van Cuylenburg, Singapore. Available from: http: // nla. gov. au / nla. obj- 231529372 (accessed 9 FJanuary F 2020)" type="url" year="1898">RASGBI 1898</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1910,2042]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,154,394]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="400" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">
Further, the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[576,779,1910,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Halobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis box="[576,779,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Halobates sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published in the series “Fasciculi Malayensis: anthropological and zoological results of an expedition to 
<collectingRegion box="[685,746,1946,1970]" country="Malaysia" name="Perak" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Perak</collectingRegion>
and the Siamese Malay States, 
<date box="[1090,1214,1946,1970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" value="1901" valueMax="1902">
<collectingDate box="[1090,1214,1946,1970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" value="1901" valueMax="1902">1901–1902</collectingDate>
</date>
”, which additionally reinforces the initial basis for this geographic misinterpretation. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A15F5D59163C3936FF7CFDDE5B5EFE3B:2C29BA94163C3937FCD7F80B5D64F867" box="[828,889,1982,2006]" country="Malaysia" name="Some" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" stateProvince="Perak">Some</location>
of the past confusion as to whether the 
<typeStatus box="[1305,1351,1982,2006]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">type</typeStatus>
locality lay in 
<collectingCountry box="[220,318,2018,2042]" name="Malaysia" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
or not may have arisen because the far southern provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[991,1089,2018,2042]" name="Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, immediately to the north of the modern Malaysian state of Perak, were for a time referred to by British authorities as the “Siamese Malay States.” This has previously caused some confusion in regard to the 
<typeStatus box="[740,786,190,214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">type</typeStatus>
locality for another water strider, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[1153,1430,190,214]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1153,1430,190,214]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Metrocoris nigrofasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was taken at Bukit Besar, near Nawngchik, which equates to modern Nong Chik, 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1205,226,250]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus, D. A." box="[1220,1391,226,250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref1041" refString="Polhemus, D. A. (1990) A revision of the genus Metrocoris Mayr (Heteroptera: Gerridae) in the Malay Archipelago and the Philippines. Entomologica scandinavica, 21, 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00012" type="journal article" year="1990">Polhemus 1990</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 22–23). This latter locality lies only 
<quantity box="[545,613,262,286]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" unit="km" value="23.0">23 km</quantity>
to the southwest of the town of Jambu shown in the map accompanying the present manuscript, and as with Jambu, was long interpreted to lie in 
<collectingCountry box="[906,1007,298,322]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. In both cases, the specimens were collected during the same expedition by Nelson Annandale and 
<collectorName box="[802,1084,334,358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Herbert C. Robinson. This</collectorName>
former colonial naming convention likely contributed to the confusion as to which Jambu was actually being referred to in the earlier literature.
</paragraph>
